description: For sale in our St. Louis showroom is a 2 owner, beautiful blue 1977 Lincoln Mark V. The odometer reads 41,260, which is the actual mileage on the car. Options for this 1977 Lincoln Mark V include: Air Conditioning, AM/FM Radio, Cruise Control, Power Brakes, Power Steering, Power Locks, Power Seats, Power Windows, Tilt Wheel, Seat Belts, Leather Interior, and White Wall Radial Tires. Powering this long blue Lincoln is the original 460 CID V8 engine, which is mated to the original 3 speed, C6 automatic transmission. A new carburetor, fuel pump, and gas tank were added during a recent tune up, as well as the white wall, radial tires that have approximately 100 miles on them. This 77' Lincoln received a respray of the original blue paint about a year ago, and looks great, as does the blue vinyl section of the roof. The light gray leather interior features blue accents throughout, and is in great condition, free from any rips, tears, or major wear. The Continental Mark V was produced and sold by the Lincoln division of Ford Motor Company from 1977 to 1979. The Mark series was a personal luxury coupe, and the Mark V was the largest version to ever be produced of any Mark series, in fact it was the largest mid-sized car ever produced. It was longer than its GM rival the Cadillac Eldorado by nearly 6 inches. During its three year production run it averaged 75,000 units sold each year, again beating the Eldorado through 1978. The Mark V differed from the Mark IV in that it featured hideaway headlights, round opera inspired windows in the sail panel, a spare tire contoured trunk lid, and the most prevalent change, the chrome plated front grille. These cars feature an incredibly long hood, 7 feet to be exact. To view this 1977 Lincoln Mark V in greater detail, including HD pictures and an HD video, visit www.GatewayClassicCars.com or our St. Louis showroom. For more information, please call 618-271-3000 or email STL@GatewayClassicCars.com

Very Nice Original 1974 Chevy Corvette L-82 Coupe

New to our Pleasanton showroom is this impressive 1974 Chevrolet Corvette L-82 2 Door Coupe with blue exterior paint, a white racing stripe and a black leather interior.  It features its factory 350 cid L82 V-8 engine under the hood with the numbers-matching four speed manual transmission, both of which have been rebuilt within the last 4,800 miles.  From what we can see, this one appears to be a true survivor with very little change over the past four decades.  It is in very nice driver condition as well and it’s priced to find a new home quickly.
Only 4,800 Miles on Rebuilt Factory Drivetrain

The current owner of this 1974 Chevrolet Corvette L-82 Coupe informs us that it’s had three total owners throughout its life.  We do have a good bit of documentation to show that it’s been properly cared for over the years as well, and this beautiful classic still manages to turn heads on the open road today.  There are some cosmetic issues in the paint and the interior so it’s obvious that this example was not a barn find or a classic kept in storage- it has been enjoyed as a daily driver for most of its life.

Additionally, this 1974 Chevrolet Corvette L-82 Coupe comes with the original owner’s manual and other documentation to add to its provenance.  With less than 5k miles on the rebuilt drivetrain, it still performs excellent and it’s ready to enjoy today.
Priced Right to Find a New Home Quickly

Overall, you’ll find that this 1974 Chevrolet Corvette L-82 Coupe is a beautiful survivor that’s seemingly withstood the tests of time in spectacular fashion.  It can be enjoyed immediately or restored back to something truly special, so the next owner is going to have quite a decision on their hands.  For more information about this vehicle, visit our Pleasanton, California showroom, give us a call at

description: 1955 Ford Sedan Delivery Wagon
The Color: Grabber Green with ghost flames and surf mural
The Interior: Custom Gray and Black
The Engine: 223 inline 6 with headers and aluminum intake
The Transmission: 4 Speed Manual
The Differential: Ford 9”
Custom stereo system
New Lemans RS radial tires
New radiator and new heater core
New complete “Painless” wiring
Converted to 12 volt system and all lights work
New instrument bezel and working clock
Accessory gauges with factory functioning fuel gauge
Tilt steering column with wood enhanced steering wheel
Interior ambiance lighting with remote control
New dual exhaust system with Dynomax mufflers
14” polished slot mag wheels with aluminum spinner centers

You really should do yourself a favor and pay attention to this exceptional Surf Wagon. This wagon is sooo cool! All the cool features aside for a moment, this thing starts, runs, drives and shifts fantastic! With its new wiring, new clear speedometer lens, as well as all new exterior lenses and head lights, this wagon's lighting system is as crisp as the custom Grabber Green paint. Couple of unique lighting ques to point out is the interior has some very cool ambiance lighting for when your cruising around at night, parked at an evening car show, or hanging around the bonfire after night surfing. The Ford script on the back bed door also lights up when the brakes are applied.

I don't want to gloss over the beautiful paint (pun intended), but the quality Grabber Green base coat, clear coat paint that just pops with the flawless stainless trim is truly a stunning eye catcher. Once you see it your lured to the wagon and begin to notice the other features this wagon has to offer.

The inline 6 cylinder engine is nicely tuned and has a few nice performance enhancements such as an aluminum intake manifold, split exhaust headers, new carburetor and electronic ignition. The engine compartment is striking, asymmetrically painted valve cover, powder-coated headers, black heater components and body colored engine surround is very “Hotrod Tasteful”. The undercarriage is very clean and free of rust. The brakes are all new, and although they are drum, they work just fine. The mural on the panel sides gives a nod to the surf culture and is removable if desired. This is one of the cleanest, finest, coolest looking wagons around.
